Skim ice surface. Little to no ice on the bottom at the mmnt section just below the gauge. 
Probable some backwater still present but not a lot of it i would suspect.
column14: Fair chop and wade mmnt downstream of the gauge 30 m. Trace flow on the edges through dead weeds. Most of the water through about half a meter of section. Some dead flow behind a weedy section upstream. Some 10%er that were unavoidable where most of the flow was.  Logger lost the shaft encoder again and is only reading error. Pulled power to start. Still could not find the shaft encoder.  Replaced the newer (blue) shaft encoder with an older (grey) one that has always worked well and never had issues as i just dont trust the newer blue ones anymore. So far it seems to be working well but could fail at any moment depending on what is causing these shafts to fail. This one is already lasting longer than the last one we tried to install which stopped working after 10 min.  Stage is rising slowly. Mid-section
